Senate Resolution 52
By: Senators Dolezal of the 27th, Still of the 48th and Anavitarte of the 31st
A RESOLUTION
1 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution so as to provide that the General Assembly may
2 by general law authorize local boards of education to impose, levy, and collect development
3 impact fees and use the proceeds to pay for a share of the cost of additional educational
4 facilities; to provide for the submission of this amendment for ratification or rejection; and
5 for other purposes.
6 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article VIII, Section VI of the Constitution is amended by adding a new Paragraph to read
9 as follows:
10 "Paragraph V. Development impact fees for educational purposes. The General
11 Assembly is authorized to provide by general law that each local board of education may
12 by resolution impose, levy, and collect development impact fees within any area of its local
13 school system which is experiencing new growth and development. A county or
14 municipality that has received a local board of education resolution imposing a
15 development impact fee shall collect such fee as a condition of development approval by
16 such county or municipality. Proceeds of any development impact fee imposed pursuant
17 to this Paragraph shall be used to pay for a share of the cost of additional educational
